sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CMV promoter, CD4 sequence with HA tag behind of signal peptide, CUb (split ubiquitin system)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: peter cimermancic

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I712004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: a constitutive expression promoter or use in mammalian cells. Ribosome binding site is included.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrej Ondracka

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CD4 signal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CD4 signal peptide; localizes to plasma membrane
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for first 25 amino acids (including start codon) of CD4 receptor which is signal peptide for plasma membrane localization.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Peter Cimermancic
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from human gene for CD4 receptor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: HA-tag is used for detection of HA-tagged proteins by anti-HA antibodies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anja Korenčič
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part was constructed by primer annealing.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Gene was designed to be constructed by primer annealing. Includes start codon.
